        <headline>Heat Advisory issued August 6 at 2:05PM MDT until August 8 at 8:00PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...High temperatures of 95 to 104 degrees are expected for
Thursday and Friday.

* WHERE...El Paso, Pueblo, and Eastern Fremont Counties.

* WHEN...For the first Heat Advisory, from 11 AM to 8 PM MDT
Thursday. For the second Heat Advisory, from 11 AM to 8 PM MDT
Friday.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures may cause heat illnesses to occur in a
short period of time.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
